WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.786 --> 00:00:02.540
BORIS DEBIC: Welcome
everybody.

00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:07.830
I am extremely pleased to
welcome today Mark Blyth.

00:00:07.830 --> 00:00:13.780
Mark Blyth will share with us
his insights into austerity as

00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:17.620
it takes shape in the
European Union.

00:00:17.620 --> 00:00:20.520
Let me read a little bit
from his biography.

00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:24.240
Mark Blyth is a faculty fellow
at the Watson Institute,

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:27.030
professor international
political economy in Brown's

00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:29.880
political science department,
and director of the

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:33.190
university's Undergraduate
Programs in Development

00:00:33.190 --> 00:00:36.000
Studies and International
Relations.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.470
He's also the author of "Great
Transformations--

00:00:39.470 --> 00:00:42.180
Economic Ideas and Institutional
Change in the

00:00:42.180 --> 00:00:43.770
20th Century."

00:00:43.770 --> 00:00:46.240
He's the editor of the
"Routledge Handbook of

00:00:46.240 --> 00:00:50.090
International Political
Economy," co-editor of a

00:00:50.090 --> 00:00:53.590
volume on constructivist theory
on political economy

00:00:53.590 --> 00:00:57.620
titled "Constructing the
International Economy," and

00:00:57.620 --> 00:01:00.380
he's working also on a new
book that questions the

00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:03.540
political and economic
sustainability of liberal

00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:06.880
democracies, called "The
End of the Liberal

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:10.110
World." That's dramatic.

00:01:10.110 --> 00:01:12.530
Blyth is a member of the
Warwick Commission on

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.770
International Financial
Reform.

00:01:14.770 --> 00:01:17.750
He is a member of the editorial
board of the "Review

00:01:17.750 --> 00:01:21.710
of International Political
Economy." And his articles

00:01:21.710 --> 00:01:25.200
have appeared in journals such
as "The American Political

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:29.090
Science Review," "Perspectives
in Politics," "Comparative

00:01:29.090 --> 00:01:32.780
Politics," and "World Politics."
He has a Ph.D. in

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:35.460
political science from Columbia
University, and

00:01:35.460 --> 00:01:41.000
taught at Johns Hopkins
University from 1997 to 2009.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.780
Please give a hand
to Mark Blyth.

00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:45.226
MARK BLYTH: Thank you.

00:01:45.226 --> 00:01:46.476
Cheers.

